Thrushes, blackbirds and kereru have regularly search for and eat the fruit in a number of kawakawa trees in this suburban garden. While harakeke was in flower here and tui were regular visitors, blackbirds and thrushes were not seen. Harakeke flowering ended about a week ago. Tui still check out the harakeke stems occasionally and briefly, and have begun to eat karamu berries a few metres away, but the blackbirds (and thrushes?) are back
